TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Measure of Styles of Handling Interpersonal Conflict
AU  - Rahim, M. Afzalur
Y1  - 1983/06/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255985
DO  - 10.5465/255985
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 368
EP  - 376
VL  - 26
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a research on various styles of handling interpersonal conflict. For the measurement of conflict styles, seven non-random samples were used to generate and select suitable items. Five factorially independent and reliable scales for conflict styles from a national sample were constructed. These were used to test further validities of the scales against the measures of role status and sex. Results indicated that the test-retest and internal consistency reliability coefficients are satisfactory and compare favorably with other existing instruments.
AB  - The article discusses a research on various styles of handling interpersonal conflict. For the measurement of conflict styles, seven non-random samples were used to generate and select suitable items. Five factorially independent and reliable scales for conflict styles from a national sample were constructed. These were used to test further validities of the scales against the measures of role status and sex. Results indicated that the test-retest and internal consistency reliability coefficients are satisfactory and compare favorably with other existing instruments.
