T1  - Evaluation Of Job Analysis Methods By Experienced Job Analysts
AU  - Levine, Edward L.
AU  - Ash, Ronald A.
AU  - Hall, Hardy
AU  - Sistrunk, Frank
Y1  - 1983/06/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255981
DO  - 10.5465/255981
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 339
EP  - 348
VL  - 26
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a research on job analysis methods being used by experienced job analysts. Job analysis is a process wherein jobs are subdivided into elements through the application of a formalized, systematic procedure for data collection, analysis and synthesis. Several job analysis methods were used in the study and evaluated by job analysts by means of a mailed questionnaire. Results indicated that opinions about job analysis are not attributable directly to specific features of a job analysis method.
AB  - The article discusses a research on job analysis methods being used by experienced job analysts. Job analysis is a process wherein jobs are subdivided into elements through the application of a formalized, systematic procedure for data collection, analysis and synthesis. Several job analysis methods were used in the study and evaluated by job analysts by means of a mailed questionnaire. Results indicated that opinions about job analysis are not attributable directly to specific features of a job analysis method.
